subject: p12185775
History: Year old woman with PICC line migrating, PICC LINe placement.
Findings: The PICC line on the right has migrated slightly more proximally with the distal lead tip now in the proximal SVC. Heart size is within normal limits. There is a left retrocardiac opacity and a small left-sided pleural effusion. There is no signs for acute pulmonary edema or pneumothoraces. Calcified granulomas are seen within the left upper lobe.
